data.title: Creating Deeper Meaning in Your Work: Stand Out While Feeling Fulfilled
data.description:
Hi, I’m Elinor! I’m so excited to be here today to show you how you can find the deeper meaning in your work and stand out as a person who inspires others at work. I’ve been working with smart women just like you for over 7 years, helping them tap into their heart’s message and use their voice to stand up and stand out as the go-to leader & expert in their field.

You will walk away with:

  • An understanding of what ‘deeper meaning’ really means in the workplace
  • How to feel fulfilled in your current role
  • Conceptualize why focusing on the deeper meaning of work will make you both happier & help you stand out

Elinor would love to know the answer to this question before the Chat & Learn!

  • What do you want to know about finding your purpose and how to create more meaning in your work?

data.title: The Emotional Bank Account: Leverage Your Network without Being Transactional
data.description:
Looking back on the last 20 years, many of the most significant aspects of my life, from career choices to spouse, started with a referral from a friend. I used to see this as good luck, or being at the right place at the right time - and of course there are elements of both. But I realize now that there are things we can do to make these kismet moments happen for ourselves - namely cultivating a community of supporters, putting intention out to our network, being able to effectively ask for what we need.

Don't forget to check your registration email for a special promo from Liweli.

In this chat I will tell you about:

  • My journey from a first generation immigrant to CBD entrepreneur
  • Share a few tips I have learned along the way about how to make serendipity happen through your network
  • Talk about the wild world of cannabis wellness

data.title: Referrals & Introductions: Who, What, When, Why, & How to Ask
data.description:
Making new friends as an adult is just like deciding what to make for dinner; it’s surprisingly (and almost universally) difficult and tedious, and no one ever seems to talk about the struggle! And if you thought making new social connections was tough, try adding the pressure of maintaining professionalism and it’s suddenly easy to understand why the art of introductions and referrals seems so murky! But Kelly Kugler, Founder & President of Allora Collective, is here to demystify this process AND help us understand how to make and use connections like this to our professional advantage!

Kelly is happy to share her expertise, but be sure to bring your questions so you can take full advantage of her knowledge! Your pre-submitted questions (during registration and leading up to the event) will help direct the direction of this chat, but you can expect to leave with these key takeaways:

  • Who to ask & when to reach out
  • What kind of connection you should make & how to ask
  • How to draft a clear message to get what you want
